headline: Erie Indemnity (ERIE): Buy, Sell, or Hold Post Q1 Earnings?
summary: Over the last six months, Erie Indemnity’s shares have sunk to $352.60, producing a disappointing 16.9% loss while the S&P 500 was flat. This was partly due to its softer quarterly results and might have investors contemplating their next move.
